{
  "stem": "893.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that military government stopped all the deportations from the capital city of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and we-- we were told that the-- that there is a relaxation of anti-Semitism in Budapest, and people sort of are breathing more easily in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The rest of the country of Hungary was already without Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we decided that maybe our chances would be better to go to Hungary than to stay in Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were making contacts with people who had-- who had to cross the border.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And our plans were definitely to leave Slovakia and go to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I-- it was Yom Kippur, after Yom Kippur, when we decided.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The day after Yom Kippur, it was in beginning of October, that we decided that we'll-- we'll go to make some contacts with someone to take us back to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We took the bus from the little town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We sort of felt more safe, safer too, even though we had to walk several miles to take a bus from next village back to Bratislava, instead of taking the train.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was a train station in that village.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we walked to the bus station, and we boarded the bus.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And our plan was to go to Bratislava to do some contacts through some Jewish friends and-- who had non-Jews-- Jewish contacts who would smuggle us over the border to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Boarded the bus.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When the bus got to the outskirts of Bratislava, the bus was stopped, was boarded by a Hungarian and a German agent, an SS person.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they announced-- they asked us to produce our identity cards.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At that point in time, we were-- everyone in Slovakia was to have had a Slovakian picture identity, ID.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
